Name: glycine N-methyltransferase deficiency
Definition: A hypermethioninemia characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of persistent isolated hypermethioninemia without cystathionine beta-synthase deficiency

Name: hypermethioninemia due to adenosine kinase deficiency
Definition: A hypermethioninemia characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of developmental delay

Name: hypermethioninemia with deficiency of S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase
Definition: A hypermethioninemia characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of psychomotor delay
Synonym: psychomotor retardation due to S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase deficiency
